        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4483514614" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6394999659984611855">I decided to read this on Monday to honor and recognize King and I’m left convicted by his prophetic words and deeply sorrowful I didn’t read these landmark speeches earlier in my life. Powerful is too small a world. To read MLK’s poetic calls to action, his unwavering spirit-led ability to look death and suffering in the face and say “I will not fear evil” for the sake of the Beloved Community, the Promised Land where there exists a brotherhood of all people, his resistance to hatred when hate </span>
  <span id="freeText6394999659984611855" style="display:none">I decided to read this on Monday to honor and recognize King and I’m left convicted by his prophetic words and deeply sorrowful I didn’t read these landmark speeches earlier in my life. Powerful is too small a world. To read MLK’s poetic calls to action, his unwavering spirit-led ability to look death and suffering in the face and say “I will not fear evil” for the sake of the Beloved Community, the Promised Land where there exists a brotherhood of all people, his resistance to hatred when hate would be so easy given the affliction he and people of color faced at every turn… it’s transformative. I’ve always revered MLK for his leadership in the civil rights movement, but these speeches helped me see him as one of the greatest leaders and examples we have in the movement to bring God’s kingdom, Jesus’ way of powerful love, to our nation and world.</span>
