<div id="review_2077158900" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2077158900" />
    <a title="Karen" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/45115034-karen"><img alt="Karen" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1601524098p2/45115034.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2077158900?book_show_action=true">Jul 30, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Karen" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Karen" href="/user/show/45115034-karen">Karen</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2077158900" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7477366755798044087">The speeches in the book deepened my appreciation of King&apos;s strategic use of language -- I would recommend it to anyone who has had little opportunity to dig into King&apos;s presentations (i.e., overexposure to the &quot;I Have a Dream&quot; text). The selected speeches, all of which are packaged with thoughtful introductions by those who knew and/or worked with King, are organized chronologically, which allows the reader to track King&apos;s developing themes and style during the prime of his activism. I included</span>
  <span id="freeText7477366755798044087" style="display:none">The speeches in the book deepened my appreciation of King's strategic use of language -- I would recommend it to anyone who has had little opportunity to dig into King's presentations (i.e., overexposure to the "I Have a Dream" text). The selected speeches, all of which are packaged with thoughtful introductions by those who knew and/or worked with King, are organized chronologically, which allows the reader to track King's developing themes and style during the prime of his activism. I included the Nobel Prize acceptance speech in communications studies with my 11th-grade students this past spring, primarily because King used the same rhetorical devices that were the focus of our unit . A number of the speeches can be viewed and heard through online sources.</span>
  <a data-text-id="7477366755798044087" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


